        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 29 at 5:46PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 545 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ellisboro, or near Madison, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Intelligence...
Ellisboro...
and Bethany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
